# Variable number of arguments in typescript
let varArgs = (...args: any[]) => {
  console.log(...args);
}
Dick move, use Objects, max 3 parameters

# Arrow fn vs Regular function difference
FEATURE               REGULAR FUNCTION   ARROW FUNCTION 
*HOISTING                  maybe            x
*this variable             .                no this, borrowed from outer scope
named functions            .                x
Anonymous function         .                always
arguments variable         .                x

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Functions/arguments

# Anonymous functions
* Is a function going to be used only once? can I reuse it?
+ good for dispatching events, we already know the name of event

# Hoisting
call a function before its deceleration

# Call by Value and Call by Reference
Call by Value         Primitives values, strings, numbers, boolean, symbol, undefined, null
Call by Reference     Objects, functions, arrays
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35606970/typescript-is-there-a-way-to-pass-parameter-to-method-by-reference/35608020
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35473404/pass-by-value-and-pass-by-reference-in-javascript

